snippet.textDisplay: my opinion, i like this new music from joji, and his old music, i think he needs to visit his older lo-fi style of music thought, it’s been a while since we’ve had a “sadder” album, now of course a lot of joji’s music has some “sadder” themes to it, (sounding sad) but i feel like his older music was definitely what drew a lot of people in, i feel like he should make a “ballads 2” where it had some sad themes, and some lighter ones, but a lot of the stuff he’s been involved in here recently is definitely not his “style” per-say or at least how a lot of us viewed his style when he started making music, i feel like he should at least touch up on it, i know it’s not difficult for him to make this both kinds of music considering his talent, but i do feel like he should make a mix album again, where it has some light and some dark, i feel it would be a very good way to bring newer fans and older ones back, i know i stopped listening to joji for a while because it wasn’t the basic lo-fi style i’m used to, but i still love his newer music, i just prefer the older more lo-fi style, but songs like run are perfect for joji as well, i do genuinely believe that joji should make a mix album where it takes songs like run and songs like demons and puts them together in a nice little album, a perfect way to bring old and new fans together, in my opinion at least

snippet.textDisplay:
Just the album cover alone is incredibly evocative and poetic. Never before have I seen an image that perfectly encapsulates the meaning and raw power of a song, but a hand reaching out of lava? Of all the fiery comparisons people have used to describe heartache, nothing is more inevitable, inescapable, or as destructive as the image of someone who is being run down by a seep of magma.
Everything about this song is golden- the beat, the album cover, the vocals, and those absolutely ENCHANTING harmonics! I’m so happy that Joji is overcoming the man who had to quit the Filthy Frank show.
snippet.textOriginal:
Just the album cover alone is incredibly evocative and poetic.  Never before have I seen an image that perfectly encapsulates the meaning and raw power of a song, but a hand reaching out of lava?  Of all the fiery comparisons people have used to describe heartache, nothing is more inevitable, inescapable, or as destructive as the image of someone who is being run down by a seep of magma. 
Everything about this song is golden- the beat, the album cover, the vocals, and those absolutely ENCHANTING harmonics!  I’m so happy that Joji is overcoming the man who had to quit the Filthy Frank show.
